The Chronicle Bongani Ndlovu, Online Reporter A DOG was seen carrying in its jaws a foetus along the Maphisa – Sun Yet Sen road in Matabeleland South with police investigating a case of baby dumping. The foetus is 24-weeks old and the harrowing discovery was at Mahetshe Village, police tweeted. “Police in Kezi are investigating a case of baby dumping alternatively unlawful termination of pregnancy following the discovery of an approximately 24 weeks old human foetus, which was carried by a dog along the Maphisa – Sun Yet Sen Road near Mahetshe Village, Maphisa,” read the tweet. The police said anyone with information to contact any nearest police station.